The problem requires converting an integer to its base -2 representation. We can solve this by repeatedly dividing the number by 2 and storing the remainders in reverse order. Since division is an operation with a logarithmic time complexity, the overall time complexity is O(log(n)). The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the StringBuilder. The energy implications are low because the solution only involves basic arithmetic operations and does not consume significant energy.

